I'll tell you what I told him.

216
00:09:35,820 --> 00:09:36,830
你说
Which was?

217
00:09:36,830 --> 00:09:38,330
我会考虑的
I'll think about it.

218
00:09:47,210 --> 00:09:48,820
我知道最近我们有些紧张
I know there's been some tension,

219
00:09:48,820 --> 00:09:51,180
而且我应该负主要责任
and I'm probably more to blame than you are.

220
00:09:51,580 --> 00:09:53,290
但过去的事就让它过去吧
But I'd like to put that behind us.

221
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,300
佐伊
Zoe,

222
00:09:55,910 --> 00:09:58,280
你将成为我们新一任驻白宫记者
you're going to be our new White House correspondent.

223
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:00,520
那简宁呢
What about Janine?

224
00:10:00,660 --> 00:10:02,800
升任中西部总编辑
I promoted her to Midwest Bureau chief.

225
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,070
她同意了吗
She's okay with that?

226
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:05,370
她舍得放弃白宫的工作
She wants to give up the White House?

227
00:10:05,370 --> 00:10:07,060
