我不知道
I don't know.

232
00:10:19,650 --> 00:10:20,890
解雇你
To fire you.

233
00:10:20,890 --> 00:10:22,300
也许吧
Maybe.

234
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,810
都过去了
Water under the bridge.

235
00:10:25,380 --> 00:10:26,800
我们要重新开始
We're starting over.

236
00:10:27,970 --> 00:10:31,020
那么  你准备好了吗
So are you ready to take this on?

237
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:34,280
我能考虑一下吗
Can I think about it?

238
00:10:35,490 --> 00:10:37,020
有一份白宫的工作摆在面前
People usually don't have to think about it

239
00:10:37,020 --> 00:10:38,250
人们一般不用考虑的  佐伊
when they're offered the White House, Zoe.

240
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:39,600
只要一两天就好
Just a day or two.

241
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:42,420
简宁将乘周五的航班飞往芝加哥
Janine is booked for a flight to Chicago on Friday.

242
00:10:42,430 --> 00:10:43,600
我会在那之前回复你
I'll let you know before then.

243
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,220
我只是要
I just need to...

244
00:10:46,190 --> 00:10:48,490
谢谢你  汤姆
Thank you. Thank you, Tom.

245
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:58,420
大卫・拉斯姆森是多数党领袖
David Rasmussen is the majority leader,

246
00:10:58,420 --> 00:10:59,870
也就是说他的职位在我之上
which means he's one step above me

247
00:10:59,870 --> 00:11:00,890
在博奇之下
and one below Birch,

248
00:11:00,890 --> 00:11:03,200
就像夹在一匹饿极的狼
which is akin to being between a very hungry wolf

249
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:04,860
和一只好斗的羊之间
and a very quarrelsome sheep.

250
00:11:04,860 --> 00:11:07,710
羊群或是狼群  看看他会选择哪一边
Let's see if he stays with the herd or joins the pack.

251
00:11:07,710 --> 00:11:09,710
大卫  不介意我坐这儿吧
David. You mind if I join you?

252
00:11:09,710 --> 00:11:12,250
请坐  就吃沙拉啊
Please. A salad, huh?

253
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:14,330
是啊  我想好好照顾自己
Yes. I'm trying to take better care of myself.

254
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:15,540
不错嘛  节食吗
Good man. Diet?

255
00:11:15,540 --> 00:11:17,940
节食  锻炼  各种方法
Diet, exercise, everything.

256
00:11:19,790 --> 00:11:22,130
你也该照顾好自己
You ought to take better care of yourself too.

257
00:11:22,130 --> 00:11:24,430
他们这儿的披萨实在太美味了
Well, they should stop serving such good pizza.

258
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:26,590
我不是指饮食
Oh, I'm not talking about the food.

259
00:11:27,330 --> 00:11:29,520
我是指博奇
I'm talking about Birch.

260
00:11:31,450 --> 00:11:33,110
你要想当上议长
You are never going to be speaker

261
00:11:33,110 --> 00:11:34,770
就必须得有所行动
unless you do something about it.

262
00:11:34,770 --> 00:11:36,750
我对自己的位置很满意
I'm very satisfied where I am.

263
00:11:36,750 --> 00:11:38,910
-拜托  -就目前来说  确实满意
- Oh, come on. - For the time being, yeah.

264
00:11:38,910 --> 00:11:40,010
一时就是永远
Time being never.

265
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:41,420
你想成为议长
The only way you become Speaker

266
00:11:41,420 --> 00:11:43,640
只有可能是博奇落选或退休
is if Birch loses his district or retires,

267
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:44,610
在你我老到要装假牙之前
neither of which is going to happen

268
00:11:44,610 --> 00:11:46,180
这两种情况都不会发生
before you and I have dentures.

269
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,230
我不喜欢你这番话的势头  弗兰克
I'm not happy where this conversation is going, Frank.

270
00:11:48,230 --> 00:11:50,260
你想做议长  我知道你想
If you want it, and I know you do,

271
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:51,890
我有个办法
there's a way.

272
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:53,770
好了  我不能...
Okay. Right. I can't...

273
00:11:53,770 --> 00:11:56,420
票数过半就可以  也就是218票
all you need is a simple majority... 218 votes.

274
00:11:56,420 --> 00:11:58,810
我们在共和党能得到205票
We're going to get at least 205 out of the G.O.P.,

275
00:11:58,810 --> 00:12:00,530
这样  再有民主党13票就行
and after that, all you need is 13 Democrats.

276
00:12:00,530 --> 00:12:01,960
你我手里就有两票
You and I make two.

277
00:12:02,310 --> 00:12:03,910
你疯了吗
Are you out of your mind?

278
00:12:05,140 --> 00:12:08,730
稍稍考虑一下吧
Just consider it for a moment.

279
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:11,280
你想和共和党串通
You want to collude with the Republicans?

280
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:12,010
我不想
I don't want to,

281
00:12:12,010 --> 00:12:14,550
但如果能让你当上议长  我会的
but I would if you become Speaker in the process.

282
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:15,790
这种事没有先例
Never been done before.

283
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:17,750
凡事都有第一次
There's a first time for everything.

284
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:18,970
这太荒谬了
This is ridiculous.

285
00:12:18,970 --> 00:12:22,400
共和党会很乐意杀杀鲍勃的威风
The Republicans would love a chance to knock Bob down a peg or two.

286
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:23,790
而你想帮他们
And you want to help them.

287
00:12:23,790 --> 00:12:25,570
我想帮我们
I want to help us.

288
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:28,350
鲍勃不会和白宫合作
Bob will not play ball with the White House.

289
00:12:28,350 --> 00:12:30,760
你是个通情达理的人  大卫  他不是
Now, you're a reasonable man, David, and he's not.

290
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:34,910
你知道我是什么人吗
You know what I am?

291
00:12:35,420 --> 00:12:37,270
我是个谨慎的人
I'm a discreet man.

292
00:12:37,270 --> 00:12:38,410
所以算你走运
You're lucky for that.

293
00:12:38,410 --> 00:12:40,290
我不会跟鲍勃说今天的事
I'm not going to mention this to Bob,

294
00:12:40,290 --> 00:12:42,210
你要是再提
but if you ever bring it up again,

295
00:12:42,210 --> 00:12:43,870
我就没办法了
I won't have a choice.

296
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:48,870
看来他选择了羊群
Looks like he opted for the herd.

297
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:56,320
克莱尔
Claire.

298
00:12:56,990 --> 00:12:58,780
我想为南苏丹项目的
I'd like to put an order for the water filters

299
00:12:58,780 --> 00:13:01,540
