You have zero testimony to add.

418
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,310
我不能这么做
I can't do that.

419
00:18:14,310 --> 00:18:15,960
你能的  彼得
Yes, you can, Peter.

420
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:17,560
我为那份证词准备了几个月
I spent months on that testimony.

421
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,900
还游说委员会  我们全体员工...
I lobbied the commission. My entire office...

422
00:18:19,910 --> 00:18:21,440
我相信你一定做得很好
I'm sure you've done splendid work,

423
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:23,780
不幸的是  这事成不了
but unfortunately it can't come to fruition.

424
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:25,430
-为什么  -这就是政治
- Why? - Politics.

425
00:18:25,430 --> 00:18:27,690
有些势力是你我无力抗衡的
There's forces bigger than either of us at play here.

426
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:29,240
那可是12000人的饭碗啊
It's 12,000 jobs.

427
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:30,390
我明白  真令人遗憾
I know. It's a shame.

428
00:18:30,390 --> 00:18:32,800
我就是保住了那家造船厂才得以当选
Keeping that shipyard open is what got me elected.

429
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,090
那些人是我的朋友
Those people are my friends.

430
00:18:34,090 --> 00:18:36,270
我来不是和你争这个的  彼得
I'm not here to debate this, Peter.

431
00:18:36,270 --> 00:18:38,340
工厂必须关闭
The base will close.

432
00:18:38,340 --> 00:18:39,530
唯一的问题是
The only question is,

433
00:18:39,530 --> 00:18:41,970
你选择长痛还是短痛
will you make it a swift death or a painful one?

434
00:18:43,430 --> 00:18:45,730
不行  我不能坐视不管
No way. I won't sit on my hands.

435
00:18:45,730 --> 00:18:48,360
这对你很难  我表示同情
I sympathize that this is gonna be difficult for you.

436
00:18:48,610 --> 00:18:50,320
现在我说不出
And I don't know how yet,

437
00:18:50,320 --> 00:18:53,150
但将来我会弥补你的  彼得
but I will make it up to you, Peter.

438
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:56,070
对于你  我是个强大的朋友
I'm a powerful friend to have right now,

439
00:18:56,580 --> 00:18:59,040
或许是你唯一的朋友
perhaps your only friend,

440
00:18:59,150 --> 00:19:01,040
别违抗我
so don't defy me.

441
00:19:13,550 --> 00:19:15,490
家庭之爱
Love of family.

442
00:19:15,490 --> 00:19:18,740
大多数政客终生都被这句口号所束缚
Most politicians are permanently chained to that slogan...

443
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:20,230
"家庭价值"
family values.

444
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:23,280
要是你和妓女厮混  又被我发现
But when you cozy up to hookers and I find out,

445
00:19:23,280 --> 00:19:25,900
你就得为这份虚伪付出代价
I will make that hypocrisy hurt.

446
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:31,920
收到我送你的礼物了吗
Did you get the present I sent you?

447
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:35,710
称不上是礼物吧
You wouldn't really call it a present.

448
00:19:35,950 --> 00:19:39,430
更像是个温柔的提醒吧
Well, more of a gentle reminder, maybe.

449
00:19:39,620 --> 00:19:41,900
不怎么温柔  挺粗暴的
Mm, more heavy-handed than gentle,

450
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:42,810
真没想到啊
which surprised me.

451
00:19:42,810 --> 00:19:44,980
这不是你的风格  弗兰西斯
It's not really your style, Francis.

452
00:19:44,980 --> 00:19:47,580
是的  我收到了
But, yes. I got it.

453
00:19:48,210 --> 00:19:49,670
我喜欢这件
I like that one.

454
00:19:50,590 --> 00:19:51,630
我也是
I do too.

455
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:53,240
但第一件更好
But the first one's better.

456
00:19:53,520 --> 00:19:54,680
是吗
You think?

457
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:56,830
明天有什么事吗
Something special tomorrow?

458
00:19:56,830 --> 00:19:59,060
亚当・嘉乐威要从纽约过来
Adam Galloway's coming down from New York.

459
00:19:59,060 --> 00:20:00,010
什么事
What for?

460
00:20:00,010 --> 00:20:01,930
我需要他的一些照片
Because I need some of his photographs

461
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:04,650
下个月无声拍卖会上要用
for the silent auction at the gala next month.

462
00:20:08,010 --> 00:20:09,650
跟雷米谈过了吗
You speak to Remy yet?

463
00:20:10,160 --> 00:20:11,400
还没有
I haven't.

464
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:16,500
如果想显得诱惑些  穿黑色那件
If you want to look inviting, wear the black one.

465
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:21,440
你好
Hello.

466
00:20:21,930 --> 00:20:25,480
好的  很好  谢谢
Oh. Okay. Great. Thanks.

467
00:20:33,090 --> 00:20:34,300
亚当
Adam?

468
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:43,860
世界瞬息万变
How is it the world keeps spinning

469
00:20:43,950 --> 00:20:46,040
你却总能走在前面
and you manage to stay ahead of it?

470
00:20:48,840 --> 00:20:49,920
大卫也同意了
David's on board with this?

471
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:51,210
这就是他的主意
It was his idea.

472
00:20:51,210 --> 00:20:52,230
那他为什么没来
Then why isn't he here?

473
00:20:52,230 --> 00:20:54,850
这事还没定下前  我们得小心
Well, we have to be careful until it's a done deal.

474
00:20:54,850 --> 00:20:55,730
我说不好  弗兰克
I don't know, Frank.

475
00:20:55,730 --> 00:20:56,810
想想看  泰瑞
Think about it, Terry.

476
00:20:56,810 --> 00:20:59,650
你会成为美国国会首位
You could become the first African-American majority leader

477
00:20:59,650 --> 00:21:02,040
非裔多数党领袖
in the United States congress.

478
00:21:02,310 --> 00:21:04,110
我们一起创造历史吧
Let's make some history.

479
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:07,640
你才不在乎什么历史呢
You don't care about history.

480
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:09,800
你找我是因为我能拉到选票
You just wanted me because I can round up the votes.

481
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:12,530
我是需要选票  但历史我也是在乎的
I need the votes, and I do care about history,

482
00:21:12,530 --> 00:21:14,260
但最重要的是  泰瑞
but most importantly, Terry,

483
00:21:14,260 --> 00:21:15,900
你有领袖风范
you know how to lead.

484
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:18,710
你成为黑人党团领袖是不无原因的
You're the head of the black caucus for a reason.

485
00:21:20,090 --> 00:21:22,210
那么大卫当议长  我当多数党领袖
So David becomes speaker, I become majority leader...

486
00:21:22,210 --> 00:21:23,940
我仍然做我的党鞭
and I stay on as whip.

487
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:26,110
你为什么不自己当多数党领袖
Why don't you want majority leader for yourself?

488
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:27,850
我对现状很满意
I'm satisfied where I am.

489
00:21:27,850 --> 00:21:29,470
或许等哪天  你做了议长
Maybe one day, when you become speaker,

490
00:21:29,470 --> 00:21:30,870
会提拔一下我
you'll bump me up.

491
00:21:31,300 --> 00:21:33,800
这种事一旦决定就没有回头路了
This is the sort of thing that there's no turning back.

492
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,880
我还能给你锦上添个花
I can throw a cherry on top.

493
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:40,510
麦喀顿基地不关闭
McCudden stays open.

494
00:21:41,870 --> 00:21:42,950
怎么做
How?

495
00:21:42,950 --> 00:21:44,480
着你不会想知道
You don't want to know how.

496
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,550
你只需要头条新闻
You just want the headline

497
00:21:45,550 --> 00:21:48,400
你保住了选区内的三千份工作
when you keep 3,000 jobs in your district.

498
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,000
-12张选票  -12张选票
- 12 votes? - 12 votes.

499
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,160
我能给你搞定10张  或许11张
I can get you 10, probably 11.

500
00:21:56,220 --> 00:21:58,000
和这样的人合作真令人振奋
It's so refreshing to work with someone

501
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,660
对到手的礼物不吹毛求疵
who will throw a saddle on a gift horse

502
00:21:59,660 --> 00:22:01,430
